The '''2014 Italian Open'''<ref name=Djokovic>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/tennis/27462782|title=Novak Djokovic beats Rafael Nadal to win Italian Open in Rome|date=18 May 2014|access-date=20 April 2018|work=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/sports/2014/05/13/novak-djokovic-returns-from-wrist-injury-by-beating-stepanek-at-italian-open.html|title=Novak Djokovic returns from wrist injury by beating Stepanek at Italian Open; Giorgi advances|date=13 May 2014|access-date=20 April 2018|work=Fox News|agency=Associated Press}}</ref><ref name=telegraph>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/tennis/atptour/10839001/Rome-Masters-final-2014-Rafael-Nadal-v-Novak-Djokovic-live.html|title=Rome Masters final 2014, Rafael Nadal v Novak Djokovic: live|date=18 May 2014|format=live commentary|access-date=20 April 2018|work=The Telegraph}}</ref> (also known as the '''2014 Rome Masters'''<ref name=telegraph/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2014-05-18/nadal-to-battle-djokovic-serena-to-meet-errani/5460246|title=Rafael Nadal, Novak Djokovic into Rome Masters final; Sara Errani, Serena Williams reach decider|date=18 May 2014|access-date=20 April 2018|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|agency=Agence France-Presse, Reuters}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/sport/tennis/tennis-djokovic-stuns-nadal-to-win-rome-masters|title=Tennis: Djokovic stuns Nadal to win Rome Masters |date=19 May 2014|access-date=20 April 2018|work=The Straits Times|publisher=Singapore Press Holdings|agency=Agence France-Presse}}</ref> and sponsored title '''2014 Internazionali BNL d'Italia''') was a tennis tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]] at the Foro Italico in [[Rome]], [[Italy]]. It was the 71st edition of the Italian Open and was classified as an [[ATP World Tour Masters 1000]] event on the [[2014 ATP World Tour]] and a [[WTA Premier tournaments|Premier 5]] event on the [[2014 WTA Tour]]. It took place from 11–18 May 2014.

